    Good lord this place is amazing. Huge flavors that comes with the huge portions of their entrees. We ordered the pork belly & grits, shrimp & grits, beignet flight, buttermilk biscuits, and a bowl of mixed fruit (...lol). Both grits entrees were incredibly tasty and rich with an array of flavors from the proteins, sauces, cheese, and tomatoes all working together. But conversely, they were heavy. I advise you to share unless you want to feel like a useless (but happy!) sloth for the rest of your day. Especially the pork belly & grits, it came with a lot of fat as well as a whole poached egg.
    The beignet flight alone is a definite must. It comes with a regular beignet and three stuffed beignets: apple-cinnamon, chocolate, and crawfish. The crawfish and chocolate were my absolute favorites. They were super tasty and the beignet itself wasn't too dense nor was it greasy. The buttermilk biscuits were flaky and worked well with the grits. The fruit bowl was pretty much an afterthought LOL, but the couple pieces I had were fresh.
    The service was quick and attentive. Nothing here is lacking, so come hungry and ready to feast!  Come early or be prepared to wait, especially during weekend brunch.
